  "body": "I've a problem with the `React.addons.CSSTransitionGroup` component.\nI use React and ES6 with babel.\n\nThis is the incriminated piece of code:\n\n```\nlet ReactCSSTransitionGroup = React.addons.CSSTransitionGroup;\n...\nreturn (\n      <div className=\"row landing\" ref=\"landing\">\n        <ReactCSSTransitionGroup transitionName=\"list\" transitionAppear={true}>\n          { this.state.showList ? <List key=\"game-list\" /> : null }\n        </ReactCSSTransitionGroup>\n```\n\n```\n.list-enter {\n    opacity: 0.01;\n  }\n\n  .list-enter.game-list-enter-active {\n    opacity: 1;\n    transition: opacity .1s ease-in;\n  }\n  .list-leave {\n    opacity: 1;\n  }\n\n  .list-leave.example-leave-active {\n    opacity: 0.01;\n    transition: opacity .1s ease-in;\n  }\n```\n\nThe entering animation works, but when `this.state.showList` is false the `List` component remains in the DOM.\nIt works (without animations obviously) without the ReactCSSTransitionGroup wrapper.\n",
